added.title: Ghost with the Most
added.description: When the Halloween Spirit is kidnapped, the Titans must team with Beetlejuice to save the holiday.

added.title: TV Knight 6
added.description: Batman is forced to go to the department store with Alfred, but runs off to watch TV with Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: Bucket List
added.description: The Titans give Starfire a bucket list of activies to accomplish.

added.title: Kryponite
added.description: When Robin explains that knowing your weakness makes you a better superhero, Starfire journeys to find hers.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: As the other Titans engage in an all out thumb wrestling war, Starfire tries to broker peace.

added.title: Ones and Zeros
added.description: The Titans build an AI robot so it will create a pizza that's never been made before.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: Robin forces the other Titans to forget their dreams and find regular, boring jobs.

added.title: Croissant
added.description: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.
Cyborg's real strength comes not from his robot parts, but from his favorite song.

added.title: Oregon Trail
added.description: The Titans get into the pioneer spirit as they head west on the Oregon Trail.

added.title: Caramel Apples
added.description: Raven and Starfire clash after Starfire creates a bond with Raven's father, while Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy struggle to return to Earth's surface after falling into a deep cavern.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Operation Tin Man
added.description: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.

added.title: Colors of Raven
added.description: A magical prism causes Raven to fragment into five distinct personalities which wreak havoc around town until the other Titans can figure out how to rejoin her.

added.title: Legs
added.description: After Robin swipes her cloak, Raven's leggy figure is revealed and she transforms into Lady Legasus; meanwhile Cyborg gets stuck in the discarded cloak, revealing a dark side of his personality.

added.title: Lord of the Poppies
added.description: Grizz and the Poppy Rangers go camping on an island, but they soon find themselves deserted.

added.title: The Mummy's Curse
added.description: The Baby Bears must return a mummy to its tomb or else they'll be cursed forever.

added.title: Band of Outsiders
added.description: A gang of streetwise kids takes Baby Ice Bear under their wing.

added.title: Tabes & Charlie
added.description: Tabes and Charlie team up to find Tabes' missing dog, Kirk.

added.title: Panda's Birthday
added.description: For Panda's Birthday, the Bears try to help Panda meet his favorite K-Pop band, Monsta X.

added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: I Am Ice Bear
added.description: After Ice Bear hits his head, Grizz and Panda notice him acting like a different person.

added.title: Go Fish
added.description: While on a fishing trip, the Bears get attacked by a giant legendary fish.

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: The Curse of Elmore
added.description: When Gumball's schoolfriend Leslie finds an old video tape, the creepy mystery of Elmore's ghostly past unfolds. Featuring spooky and hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: The Vegging
added.description: Gumball and Darwin want to have a lazy day on the sofa, and have come up with various tricks to stop themselves having to move. Gradually more and more people arrive, seemingly to get them to move, until finally they realize that if they have to move, they'll do it in the laziest way possible.

added.title: The Potion
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that Hector is not so happy being giant-sized. So they decide to help him by creating a potion that will shrink him down to the size of an average person. However creating a magic potion is not as easy as it sounds, and the results can go spectacularly wrong...

added.title: The Catfish
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin realise Grandpa Louie has no friends on Elmore Plus, they feel bad so they create one called Muriel. However when Granny Jojo finds out Louie has been spending time online with another 'woman', Muriel not existing isn't going to stop her from being destroyed.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: The Menu
added.description: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell them what it's called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

added.title: The Name
added.description: When Mom reveals Gumball's real name is Zach, Gumball adopts a cheesy, annoying persona to match the name. His family tries to make him remember the old Gumball as this new Zach persona is progressively taking over Gumball's life and erasing his memories. If they can't reach him in time, the old Gumball will disappear forever and they'll be left with Zach!

added.title: The Man
added.description: It's Granny Jojo's Birthday and she's brought an unexpected guest to dinner. Granny Jojo has brought a boyfriend to her birthday meal and Dad isn't happy about it. He bans Granny JoJo from ever seeing Louis again. When the kids get caught sneaking Granny Jojo out of the house, Dad challenges Louis to a man-off to prove once and for all who is the man of the house?!!

added.title: The Oracle
added.description: Banana Barbara has made a prophecy which Gumball simply cannot accept. Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Banana Joe's mom paints pictures which predict the future. When they find one that depicts Gumball running naked through the mall, Gumball is determined not to let it come to pass. However events conspire against him, and Gumball learns that sometimes you can't fight fate.

added.title: The Nobody
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover they have an uninvited house guest. Things keep going missing in the house, so it's up to Gumball and Darwin to find the culprit. They discover that a mysterious person has been secretly living in their home. Gumball and Darwin manage to turn this confused squatter into their mortal enemy . . .

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

added.title: The Painting
added.description: Principal Brown tries to "fix" Gumball's dysfunctional family.

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: The Microwave
added.description: Gumball and Darwin accidentally create a loveable monster that eats their family.

added.title: The Meddler
added.description: Gumball is embarrassed when Mom comes to school to spend some "quality time".

added.title: Something I Ate
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max go on a tour of the impervious Fort Knox, but when Dr. Animo sicks a hungry ani-mutate on the Fort, Ben must stop it before it gobbles up the nation's monitory standard!

added.title: Steam is the Word
added.description: In the heart of Silicon Valley, Ben has to stop Victorian villain Steam Smythe from securing an epic power source sealed in a Tesla time capsule.

added.title: The Beast Inside
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Max make a return to Max's alma mater but this time it's no homecoming. Dr. Animo has made a scary transformation and found a way to release the very dangerous animal nature of humans, including Max's life-long friend!

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Trick or Creek
added.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

added.title: Memories of Bobby
added.description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
added.description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

added.title: Kelsey the Elder
added.description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

added.title: Sour Candy Trials
added.description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Bug City
added.description: Craig discovers a bunch of bugs under a rock and decides to build them a city.

added.title: Deep Creek Salvage
added.description: The Trio finds gold in the muddy depths of the Creek so Craig builds a rig to recover it.

added.title: The Shortcut
added.description: An unusually hot day at the Creek melts all of Kit's ice pops, so Craig helps her find a short cut to her frozen snack supplier before everyone else melts.

added.title: Dibs Court
added.description: When a kid claims dibs on the Stump, Craig has no choice but to take them to court. Dibs Court.

added.title: The Great Fossil Rush
added.description: JP finds a fossil in the Creek which quickly causes the landscape to change.

added.title: The Mystery of the Timekeeper
added.description: When the Time Keeper goes missing, Craig and his friends take up the task of helping kids get home in time for dinner.

added.title: Alone Quest
added.description: Craig has an "emergency" leaving Kelsey alone at the Stump.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: Duck Duck Juice
added.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

added.title: Cluckwork Orange
added.description: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bad bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: The Date
added.description: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, this gives Owen & Jude the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

added.title: Apple & Onion's Booth
added.description: Apple and Onion must save their favorite booth at Pizza's Diner from a Texas oil tycoon.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion have to get Falafel's beloved rooster back from scientists.

added.title: Pat on the Head
added.description: Apple must unhypnotize Onion before they can cook for a very important guest.

added.title: Falafel's Glory
added.description: Apple & Onion must win a trivia game to get the world's largest meatball.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: Apple and Onion must find a way to use Burger's trampoline without making him feel used.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Apple and Onion must conquer their obsessions of sausages and a video game.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion have to prove that they're not selfish when they do their good deeds.

added.title: Falafel's in Jail
added.description: Apple & Onion must get Falafel out of jail for a crime he did not commit.

added.title: Rotten Apple
added.description: Apple and Onion try to convince Onion's Dad that Apple is not a bad influence.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: Level Thirteen
added.description: Cyrus Borg discovers a shocking secret about Prime Empire, while the ninja battle an escaped Mechanic in their attempt to reach Level Thirteen and enter the game themselves.

added.title: Superstar Rockin' Jay
added.description: Now inside the Prime Empire game, the ninja find themselves in unfamiliar territory, ignorant of the rules of this world, as they try to find Zane and escape Unagami's army of Red Visors.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Love at First Bite
added.description: Val crushes on a girl named Matty, who Vic is suspicious of but Val ignores his warnings. When Val goes to dinner at her house she turns into a Matlazihua and he discovers he's what's for dinner!

added.title: Go With the Flow
added.description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: #TheBirdAndTheBee
added.description: Meek little Karen Beecher is intimidated by big broody Carter Hall - both as a hero and a teen - until she discovers Hawkman's tragically romantic destiny and vows to use her vast knowledge of cheesy teen movies to help him reunite with his beloved.

added.title: #FantasticBeastsAndHowToMindThem
added.description: Diana Prince receives a care package from home, and her pet-raising skills are soon put to the test when a mysterious egg hatches into a baby griffin.

added.title: Sword Heist
added.description: When a local sword shop sells an ultra powerful sword to Ratar-O, Lion-O decides he has to steal it before Ratar-O can come pick it up. Unfortunately Lion-O is completely against stealing, but luckily he knows someone who loves to steal, Lion-S!

added.title: Claudus
added.description: Lion-O's dad King Claudus arrives on Third Earth, and turns out to be a big selfish jerk! Now Lion-O has to deal with his dad before he goes to war with the rest of the Thundercats.

added.title: Telethon
added.description: In order to save the Berbils, Cheetara uses her psychic powers to project a telethon into the brains of everyone on Third Earth.

added.title: Mall-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra builds a mall that's actually a giant labyrinth designed to trap the Thundercats forever. Too bad the Thundercats love the mall so much they could literally spend all eternity there.

added.title: Eclipsorr
added.description: Third Earth's sun is being blocked out by the Eclipsor Corporation, an amoral company that wants to sell its energy for a profit. The ThunderCats can't do anything about it because they don't have a spaceship, yet!

added.title: Wizz-Ra
added.description: The ThunderCats freak out when a spooky ghost dressed like a pharaoh appears in their mirrors! They quickly set about to getting rid of every reflective surface in their lair, because that ghost is scary and no one wants to talk to him!

added.title: ThunderDogs
added.description: The Thundercats agree to foster a demonic puppy from the Astral Plane until they can find it the perfect owner. But could the perfect owner be their worst enemy? Their worst enemy is Mumm-Ra in case you forgot!

added.title: Mini Mongor
added.description: The Thunderkittens unleash a demon who is powered by fear. Too bad he's small and not that scary.

added.title: Study Time
added.description: Lion-O never pays attention during Tygra's training sessions so when he's asked to do a pop quiz on "sword magic" he accidentally opens a portal to the Astral Plane and releases the Nether Witch! The Witch imprisons Lion-O and Tygra in her nightmare realm and it's gonna take a lot of studying to figure out a way home. Wonder if the Astral Plane has any great teachers lying around.

added.title: Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living
added.description: Every time Mumm-Ra gets a hold of a magic artifact to restore his powers, the ThunderCats just smash it and turn him into a dinky skeleton again. Until today that is, because Mumm-Ra just remembered he's got the Ancient Spirits of Evil, and now he can get swole whenever he wants!

added.title: Berserkers
added.description: The Cats' Lair is attacked by gold-loving robot pirates, the Berserkers! This is a good thing, really, since it means Lion-O and the ThunderKittens can ditch their chores and fight robo-pirates instead! Just don't tell Tygra!!!!

added.title: Jaga History
added.description: Freed from the Astral Plane, Jaga, ghost of the ThunderCats mentor, is now free to visit the Cats' Lair. Which means he can finally tell them why Thundera, their home world, exploded. It's story time!

added.title: Now We're Only Falling Apart
added.description: Pearl tells a story.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Made of Honor
added.description: Steven has a big surprise for the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Legs from Here to Homeworld
added.description: Steven travels to visit family.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: With many changes going on in his life, Steven tries to find his place in the world.

added.title: Together Alone
added.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: Gem Glow
added.description: Steven thinks his favorite ice cream sandwiches are the trick to summoning his magic shield but learns otherwise when facing off with an acid-spewing insect monster.

added.title: Laser Light Cannon
added.description: A magical comet hurtles toward Beach City, and Steven must dig through his father's collection of old junk, and the past, to find the weapon that can save the town.

added.title: Cheeseburger Backpack
added.description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

added.title: Together Breakfast
added.description: Steven tries to get the Gems to take part in his special breakfast tradition, but instead finds himself tumbling through the magical catacombs of the Crystal Gem's temple.

added.title: Frybo
added.description: Steven helps a Boardie kid with his grueling job by using a magical gem shard that can bring clothing to life.

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: No Shortcuts
added.description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Mao Mao's Bike Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao underestimates enemy and friend alike, it almost costs him the entire kingdom.

added.title: The Perfect Couple
added.description: When Mao Mao accidentally breaks up the most perfect couple in Pure Heart Valley, he has to figure out how to get them back together.

added.title: Adoradad
added.description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.

added.title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
added.description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.

added.title: Zing Your Heart Out
added.description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.

added.title: Strange Bedfellows
added.description: After an insane battle, MM and OS end up in the same hospital room. But even in full body casts, the sworn enemies continue the fight.

added.title: Angel Face
added.description: BMO ropes his friends into a live action cowboy role-playing adventure!

added.title: Food Chain
added.description: On a field trip to the Candy Kingdom Museum of Natural History, Finn and Jake learn about the food chain by becoming the food chain!

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake and Prismo watch from the portal as the Ice King's crown makes Finn more and more powerful.

added.title: Little Dude
added.description: While Finn and Jake go swimming, Finn's hat magically comes to life!

added.title: Princess Potluck
added.description: Ice King gets super jealous when he finds out that he wasn't invited to the Princess Potluck.

added.title: Candy Streets
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess is robbed and faints before she can tell Finn and Jake who robbed her.

added.title: Time Sandwich
added.description: Jake crafts the most delicious sandwich ever, but when Magic Man steals it, Finn must defy the laws of space and time to win back Jake's creation.

added.title: Root Beer Guy
added.description: Root Beer Guy works a boring job during the day and tries to write mystery stories at night. But his life is about to change when he witnesses Finn and Jake kidnapping Princess Bubblegum!

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn and Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: Too Young
added.description: Princess Bubblegum's uncle attempts to usurp Ooo's throne.

added.title: Adventure Time with Fionna and Cake
added.description: It's a parallel universe where we explore the adventures of Fiona and Cake from the land of Aaa!

added.title: The Other Tarts
added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: The Pods
added.description: Finn and Jake must sort out the good magic beans from the bad.

added.title: The Witch's Garden
added.description: Jake loses his powers to a witch.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays Part 1
added.description: Unikitty and the gang secretly throw Master Frown the birthday of his dreams, but their efforts have lasting repercussions beyond Frown's special day.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays Part 2
added.description: Following the events of Master Frown's birthday, Unikitty and her friends form a resistance group to restore the Unikingdom.

added.title: Bedtime Stories
added.description: When Puppycorn can't fall asleep, Dr. Fox uses an invention to bring classic bedtime stories to life. But the gang's presence leads to some surprising twists in these popular tales.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Birthday Blowout
added.description: Puppycorn's birthday wish is stolen by Master Frown, the biggest downer in the kingdom! To recover it, Unikitty and Puppycorn will have to venture into the most depressing land ever, Frown Town! Will they manage to recover the birthday wish from Frown before his wish (and all wishes) are wished away forever?

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: La mascara del engano
added.description: Cuando un sindicato de criminals desconocido amenaza a la Familia Real, los ninjas son llamados de nuevo a la acción y deben proteger a la princesa real y un artefacto legendario que puede tener poderes sobrenaturales.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Mask of Deception
added.description: When an unknown criminal syndicate threatens the Royal Family, the Ninja are called back into action and must protect the royal princess and a fabled artifact that may hold supernatural powers.

added.title: La princesa de jade
added.description: A raíz de un cruel ataque al Palacio, Los Hijos de Garmadon roban la segunda Máscara Oni, y los ninjas invitan a la Princesa Real, Harumi, a su improvisada familia.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Jade Princess
added.description: In the wake of a vicious attack upon the palace, the Sons of Garmadon steal the second Oni Mask, and the ninja invite the royal princess, Harumi, into their makeshift family.

added.title: El oni y el dragon
added.description: Mientras que la Princesa Harumi se adapta a la vida con los ninjas, Lloyd y Jay buscan respuestas sobre las máscaras Oni, mientras que Cole y Zane intentan infiltrarse en Los Hijos de Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Oni & the Dragon
added.description: While Princess Harumi adjusts to life with the ninja, Lloyd and Jay search for answers about the Oni Masks, while Cole and Zane attempt to infiltrate the Sons of Garmadon.

added.title: Guar serpiente
added.description: Para unirse a Los Hijos de Garmadon, Zane (alias Jaguar Serpiente) participa en una carrera de iniciación mortal de motocicletas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Snake Jaguar
added.description: In order to join the Sons of Garmadon, Zane (aka Snake Jaguar) participates in a deadly motorcycle initiation race.

added.title: El chillido de hombre muerto
added.description: La casi desaparición de Zane a manos del Señor "E" obliga a los ninjas a huir a bordo del Bounty, donde descubren que una tramisión que Zane interceptó puede revelar la ubicación oculta del "Silencioso".
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dead Man's Squall
added.description: Zane's near demise at the hands of Mr. E forces the ninja to flee aboard the Bounty, where they discover that a transmission Zane intercepted may reveal the hidden location of the Quiet One.

added.title: La Pocion
added.description: Gumball y Darwin usan una poción mágica para encoger a Héctor.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Ken 10
added.description: We're back in the future with Ben 10K, and this time he has a son, Ken. On Ken's tenth birthday, Ben gives him his very own Omnitrix. Ben must come to learn to trust Ken with the power of the Omnitrix. Along the way, Ken befriends a kid named Devlin. Devlin turns out to be Kevin 11's son and was merely using Ken so he could break his dad out of the Null Void. Ben 10K and Ken then team up to take down Kevin 11. As for Devlin, he comes to realize his dad is a jerk, and realizes the error of his ways. He's able to redeem himself, proving he's a good kid and joining forces with "Team Tennyson."

added.title: Goodbye and Good Riddance
added.description: Summer's over and Ben is back at school. Unable to tell anyone that's he all these cool aliens that they've heard about all summer, Ben suddenly realizes he's gone from a "hero" to a "zero", that is until Vilgax comes after him with a vengeance. Ben must now reveal his hero side to his parents and to his fellow classmates. In doing so he saves his town and teams up with his dad to destroy Vilgax once and for all. But there is some bad news...Gwen has switched schools and is in Ben's class!

added.title: Battle for Cybertron I Part 1
added.description: As the Autobots on the Ark prepare to land on Cybertron, Chromia and Perceptor attempt to escape Decepticon captivity.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron I Part 2
added.description: Chromia and Perceptor race to warn the Autobots that the Decepticons are waiting for them on Cybertron.

added.title: KO, Rad, and Enid!
added.description: When confronted with their lack of a team gimmick, KO, Rad, and Enid wonder what their group identity should be.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron II Part 1
added.description: Megatron's jubilation at destroying the Ark is short-lived as he realizes the ship was a decoy — the Autobots have landed on Cybertron.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron II Part 2
added.description: The Autobots distract the Decepticons with an all-out assault on the Threshold of the Well while Bee, Hot Rod, and Cheetor split off for the real mission…

added.title: Chip's Damage
added.description: Elodie enlists KO to help figure out what to do about Chip Damage.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron III Part 1
added.description: While the battle rages on the surface, deep below ground Hot Rod faces off against an unexpected traitor, giving Cheetor and Bee time to get the Allspark to the Well.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron III Part 2
added.description: Windblade, Wheeljack, and Teletraan-X make a play for Vector Sigma.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: You're a Good Friend, KO
added.description: KO brings Dendy along for a hero mission in order to cheer her up.

added.title: Superstar Dan/Awesome Brawlers on Vacation
added.description: Superstar Dan: The Awesome Brawler's head to Tokyo for the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition. While Wynton, Shun, Lia and Lightning see the sites, and enjoy the tastes of Japan, Dan, as the Los Volmos Champion, has official Bakugan Battle League duties and obligations that keep him busy./Awesome Brawlers on Vacation: Lia, Lightning, Shun and Wynton explore the sights of Toyko when a rogue Bakugan shows up and rampages. The Awesome Brawlers have to spring into action, rolling out their Bakugan to stop the rogue enemy before any real damage can be done.

added.title: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition/Battle Royal
added.description: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes./Battle Royal: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

added.title: The Second Stage Begins/Mechanoids Attack!
added.description: The Second Stage Begins: With half of the brawlers eliminated, the second stage of the Bakugan Battle league begins. This round will be a timed race to the finish, with all kinds of tricks and traps that will slow down even the best brawlers./Mechanoids Attack!: Mechanoids have crashed the second stage of the Bakugan Battle League, causing all kinds of havoc. The Awesome Brawlers will now have to race against the clock, battling competitors and mechanoids if they want to make it through this round.

added.title: The Other Fight
added.description: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League. Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Dash/The Final Stage
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Dash: With Dan and Ajit eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition, the remaining Awesome Brawlers - Shun, Wynton, Lia and Lightning race to complete the second stage of the competition. In order to make it to the final stage, the gang will have to pull together to defeat some tough competition./The Final Stage: It's the final stage of the Bakugan Battle League Tokyo Edition! The remaining Awesome Brawlers are ready to go, but just as the final round begins, the competitors are surprised with some unwelcome guests.

added.title: Recuerdos de Bobby
added.description: Cuando un importante miembro de la comunidad del Arroyo se marcha, el trío lamenta su pérdida recordando los buenos tiempos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Jacob del Arroyo
added.description: Un terrible corte de cabello obliga a Craig a visitar el Arroyo de encubierto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: El Regreso de los Guardabosques Madreselva
added.description: Craig descubre que los Guardabosques Madreselva se han infiltrado en su lado del Arroyo para robar su posesión más preciada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Kelsey la Anciana
added.description: Una discusión entre los Ancianos del Arroyo deja un lugar vacante en su juego de rol de mesa, así que Kelsey se une a la campaña.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Peeps
added.description: Benson gets surveillance cameras to keep track of Mordecai and Rigby on the job.

added.title: Dulce Acido
added.description: Craig se embarca en un alucinante viaje mientras trata de comer la golosina más ácida del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: This is My Jam
added.description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Nacho Cheese
added.description: Pizza Steve's father comes to visit the gang and almost immediately gets on their nerves with his over the top antics. Pizza Steve must get rid of his dad, and prove to himself that he doesn't need to live in his father's shadow any longer.

added.title: Ventila-hala
added.description: Chef le confisca la mega-bola a Owen y la guarda en su oficina. Duncan, viendo una oportunidad para conseguir ayuda escapando de la guardaería, lidera un equipo de fuga por los conductos del aire acondicionado para recuperarla.

added.title: Jugo arcoiris
added.description: Después de desafiarse unos a otros a tomar el Latte de Pegaso de Chef, Izzy y Jude están llenos de energía y Duncan y Courtney hacen un viaje por carretera para tratar de reemplazar la bebida antes de que Chef descubra que desapareció.

added.title: El pollo maniaco
added.description: Después de hacerse amigo de un pollo con mala actitud en un zoológico de contacto, este lo sigue de regreso a la escuela. Él defiende la mala conducta del ave hasta que ya no puede seguir haciéndolo.

added.title: Chile libre
added.description: Cuando Owen oculta un walkie talky dentro de su perro con chile, Harold cree que es un alienígena que vino a destruir la tierra.

added.title: La cita
added.description: Cuando Chef está feliz ordena pizza para los niños. Esto le da a Owen & Jude la idea de crear una falsa admiradora secreta para Chef.

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: Un Episodio Muy Especial
added.description: Cuarzo Arcoíris 2.0 prometió cuidar de Cebolla el mismo día que Heliolita programó una charla sobre la seguridad del hogar. ¿Es posible para Steven estar en dos lugares a la vez y ser dos fusiones al mismo tiempo?

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: Escondidas
added.description: Unikitty se enorgullece de ser la campeona del Día de la escondida. Pero cuando encuentra a todos en el reino excepto a Richard, lo busca a toda costa. ¿Seguirá Richard eludiendo a la princesa en su juego favorito y, si es así, cómo lo hará?

added.title: Algo Que Comi
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max van de paseo al impenetrable Fort Knox, pero cuando el Doctor Ánimo hace que un animal-mutante hambriento se enferme, iBen debe detenerlo antes de que se devore la reserva monetaria de la nación!

added.title: Vapor Es La Palabra
added.description: En el corazón de Silicon Valley, Ben debe impedir que Vapor Smythe, el villano victoriano, consiga una fuente de poder épica sellada en una cápsula del tiempo diseñada por Tesla.

added.title: La Bestia Interior
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max regresan a la universidad de Max, pero esta vez no les dan una cálida bienvenida. El Doctor Ánimo ha hecho una transformación escalofriante y ha descubierto un modo de liberar la peligrosa naturaleza animal de los seres humanos...iincluida la del amigo de toda la vida de Max!

added.title: Todo Mojado
added.description: Nadie le cree a Ben cuando insiste en que uno de los demás clientes que aguarda en la fila del parque acuático es la malvada Frightwig disfrazada de niña común. Por eso, Ben debe demostrar que dice la verdad mientras protege a los asistentes al parque del plan maestro de la villana: idestruir el parque con su propia presión acuática!

added.title: Hora De Ser Villano
added.description: Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para evitar un desastre en la represa Hoover, pero cuando Tim Buktu, el heroico tipo rudo, se precipita para ayudar, Ben debe descubrir si Tim es su amigo...o su enemigo.

added.title: Bros in Space
added.description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

added.title: La Zona
added.description: A Unikitty le cuesta mantener la calma cuando juega a videojuegos y entra en La Zona, a diferencia de Puppycorn, su hermano menor. Pero un repentino accidente de laboratorio destroza su consola y ahora, para su sorpresa, el castillo se bloquea como un videojuego del mundo real, icon sus amigos como jugadores! ¿Podrá Unikitty salvar a sus amigos y dominar La Zona antes de que termine el juego?

added.title: Vida Ecologica
added.description: Cuando un vendedor moderno en un almacén avergüenza a los Osos por pedir bolsas de plástico, los Osos se dan cuenta de que las bolsas de tela ecológicas son su forma de lograr aceptación entre las personas progresistas del Área de la Bahía. Pero en su esfuerzo por conseguir popularidad, los Osos dejan que la cultura (y la cantidad) de bolsas de tela se apodere de sus vidas.

added.title: Charlie Y La Serpiente
added.description: Charlie (alias Pie Grande) es un tipo solitario a quien, como a los Osos, le gustaría encontrar un lugar en el mundo. En su intento por conseguirlo, Charlie organiza una fiesta, pero termina embarcándose en una aventura con el más improbable de los animales: una serpiente salvaje.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Video Cita
added.description: Panda es un ávido salidor de citas por Internet, y cuando una adorable mujer francesa coincide con él y accede a tener una cita virtual con video, Panda y sus hermanos manejan la situación para poder mostrar su mejor perfil en el video, aunque ese perfil sea absolutamente exagerado.

added.title: Tienda De Mascotas
added.description: En este episodio sobre los primeros años de vida de los Osos, se cuenta la historia del lugar en el que vivieron alguna vez cuando eran bebés. Luego de un altercado con el equipo que filmaba un video absolutamente conmovedor de adopción de animales, los Osos por poco aprovechan la oportunidad de encontrar hogares alejados uno del otro.

added.title: Chloe Y Polar
added.description: Un día, Chloe sale sola a pasear con Polar y se da cuenta de que Polar se la pasa haciéndoles recados a sus hermanos. Decidida a mostrarle cómo pasarla bien en la ciudad, Chloe promete ayudar a que Polar se divierta... Aunque eso signifique quedarse dentro de un museo después de la hora de cierre.

added.title: Double Cross
added.description: Batman has Plastic Man disguise himself as Two-Face in order to set a trap for Deadshot. Unfortunately things get complicated when the real Two-Face escapes custody.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: While You Were Away
added.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Secret Swapper of Doom
added.description: When the girls get a Paper Fortune Teller that can predict the future if they tell it a secret, they begin to rely on it to predict everything. But when it predicts the Powerpuff Girls will be destroyed, the girls must find a way to stop the future from happening.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: Superman's Pal, Sid Sharp
added.description: When obnoxious reporter Sid Sharp decides that Clark Kent is getting all his stories because of his connection to Superman, Sid decides to become his own superhero to out scoop him.

added.title: The Brain Buster
added.description: A mysterious creature abducts Batman, Mr. Terrific, Luthor and two of the brainiest villains in the universe to put them to the test to discover who is the smartest among them.

added.title: It's Chemistry, Man
added.description: Chemistry Man lays siege to Silicon Central when he discovers that his replacement, Miss CHO, has been presented with a teaching award.

added.title: Flower Power
added.description: Mega Man must battle Wood Man for the fate of the Corpse Flower, a rare and noxious bloom that's stinking up all of Silicon City.

added.title: Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: When a grudge match between Fire Man and Namagem threatens to level Silicon City, Mega Man must intervene and ultimately choose a side to prevent collateral damage.

added.title: Old School
added.description: Mega Man must stop Chaotique from making Silicon Central disappear, as in literally erasing the school at a subatomic level, while learning life lessons from a rambling old-bot named Hal.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Diary
added.description: When his diary winds up in the hands of Mr. Gus, Pizza Steve goes to great lengths to get it back before Mr. Gus can read all of his deepest, darkest secrets.

added.title: To Tame the Perilous Skies!
added.description: With Axel's drone-wing broken, the team must find another way to stop Madcap and his minions as they take to the skies in toy airplanes for an aerial assault on the city park.

added.title: This Is Not a Drill
added.description: Mega Man and Dr. Light must set aside a father-son disagreement to stop Drill Man from taking revenge on his own overbearing father.

added.title: Four Color Fallout
added.description: Axel, Galileo, and Sarge get Minergy-transported by Madcap into the pages of Axel's favorite comic book, the hero of which turns out not to be so cool after all.

added.title: Barehanded
added.description: When Green Lantern leaves his ring in an intergalactic restroom after washing his hands, he discovers it's gone, leading him on a wild chase for the aliens who might have taken it.

added.title: Unleashed
added.description: While the Justice League is away on a mission, Plastic Man is not only left in charge of the Watchtower, but also Superman's dog, Krypto.

added.title: Sin Atajos
added.description: Tras esforzarse por mantener el ritmo en las batallas, Adorabat consigue una armadura cibernética. ¿Pero podrán unos nuevos y sofisticados poderes compensar la falta de experiencia?

added.title: Ultracolosal
added.description: Colosal se vuelve enorme para destruir a un monstruo altísimo, pero cuando se rehúsa a volver a su tamaño normal, el reino se enfrenta a un nuevo terror… el apetito insaciable de Colosal.

added.title: La Aventura Perfecta
added.description: Cuando a Mao Mao se le antoja vivir la aventura perfecta, Adorabat dice una mentira piadosa.

added.title: La Aventura de la Moto de Mao Mao
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao subestima por igual a sus enemigos y a sus amigos, por poco le cuesta el reino entero.

added.title: Te Quiero Mao Mao
added.description: Un solitario explosivo y su mejor amigo holgazán se desvían del viaje que los llevará a convertirse en leyenda y descubren que su historia apenas comienza.

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: Stray Bullet
added.description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea?: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Los reyes de los Churros
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val comienzan a hacer dinero con la venta de churros en el puesto de tacos, su deseo por objetos los obliga a emplear trucos sucios para eliminar a la competencia.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: Duelo de globos
added.description: Cuando Vic es traicionado durante una guerra de globos de agua, emprende una vengativa misión para descubrir al responsable.

added.title: Amor a primera mordida
added.description: A Val le gusta una chica llamada Matty, y Vic sospecha de ella, pero Val ignora sus advertencias. Cuando Val va a su casa a cenar, ella se convierte en una Matlazihua, iy Val descubre que él es la cena!

added.title: Sigue la corriente
added.description: Cuando Sal se queda en lo de Vic y Val, los chicos no lo soportan como compañero, pero finalmente descubren lo genial y mágico que es.

added.title: Let's Fight to the End
added.description: When a fighting tournament is announced at the Plaza, there is more at stake than meets the eye.

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Soda Genie
added.description: When KO, Rad, and Enid find a soda bottle with a genie in it, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Let's Be Heroes
added.description: When KO tags along with his mom to work, he discovers the convenience store next door is his key to becoming a great hero.

added.title: We Messed Up
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid accidentally break one of Mr. Gar's prized possessions!

added.title: Sibling Rivalry
added.description: When a new robot, Raymond, defeats the three heroes to steal the sign to Gar's, KO teams up with Darrell and Shannon to get it back.

added.title: Just Be a Pebble
added.description: KO eats a piece of new candy at Gar's that makes him giant.

added.title: We've Got Pests
added.description: KO, Rad & Enid have to deal with tiny pests wreaking havoc in the bodega.

added.title: The Perfect Meal
added.description: KO teams up with Beardo to make the perfect meal for Carol.

added.title: Dweller in the Depths Part 1
added.description: When a mysterious shark-bot named Hammerbyte kidnaps comatose Windblade, Bee and Chromia must chase him into the depths of the Argon Sea to retrieve her.

added.title: Dweller in the Depths Part 2
added.description: Optimus receives a dire warning from the Primes as Chromia and Bee pursue Windblade into a waking Titan under the sea.

added.title: Silent Strike Part 1
added.description: Optimus and the Autobots infiltrate Decepticon Territory to destroy the Dark Matrix Megatron stole from a mysterious bot known only as "The Other One."

added.title: Silent Strike Part 2
added.description: Megatron tries desperately to prevent The Other One from entering their universe.

added.title: The Other One Part 1
added.description: The Other One and his Super Soldiers arrive, forcing Optimus and Megatron to fight together.

added.title: The Other One Part 2
added.description: The Other One reveals himself as an all-powerful Megatron from a universe where Optimus Prime is no more.

added.title: Talent Show
added.description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: Clarence the Movie
added.description: When Clarence starts to play around with his home video camera, he becomes increasingly drawn into the world of filmmaking. From talking toys, to real actors, to documentary subjects, Clarence is determined to find the right style to tell his story!

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Brains TV
added.description: After a marathon of classic sitcom episodes, Clarence becomes stuck as alter-ego "Clarry," an obnoxiously overacting sitcom version of himself. It's up to his friends and family to help him snap out of it, or face life with a new Clarence.

added.title: Etiquette Clarence
added.description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

added.title: Video Store
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

added.title: Anywhere but Sumo
added.description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
added.description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
added.description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

added.title: Worship
added.description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Save the Date
added.description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: Toy Ploy
added.description: When Mojo kidnaps the girls' favorite snuggle toys, he gets more than he bargained for.

added.title: Bubbles the Blue
added.description: When Bubbles isn't her normal, bubbly self, her sisters don't know how to handle it.

added.title: Man Up 3: The Good, the Bad, and the Manly
added.description: After Bubbles gets blasted with Man Boy's beard ray, she wreaks havoc in the most manly and adorable way possible.

added.title: Aliver
added.description: The Girls compete for the title of World's Greatest Superheroes!

added.title: The Status of Cattus
added.description: The Warriors want someone to enjoy collecting Magiswords as much as they do, so they go crazy trying to interest Cattus the Oneblade into obtaining more.

added.title: Get That BORFL!
added.description: A restful chill day for the Warriors and Princess Zange in the Royal Spa gets upended when a cute little Borfl runs amok throughout Castle Rhyboflaven, with the Warriors resorting to Magiswords to thwart the critter.

added.title: The Saga of Robopiggeh!
added.description: A botched rescue attempt damages their robot pal, RoboPiggeh, and Vambre and Prohyas must battle the evil cyborg, Tera-Bite, in Galacton, who is determined to dismantle their broken pal for being obsolete.

added.title: School's In, Oh Bummer
added.description: It turns out that Vambre and Prohyas didn't graduate the Adventure Academy after all and need to go back to school earn their diplomas!

added.title: Quest for Knowledge
added.description: After a flashback where we learn the origins of the Warriors passion for Magiswords, they return to Adventure Academy where Professor Cyrus sets V and P and their former classmates on a quest to find the Legendary Knowledge Magisword.

added.title: Lunch Break
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to finish a ten-foot sub.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: Rigby in the Sky with Burrito
added.description: Rigby wants to accomplish at least one thing he said he would accomplish before his High School reunion.

added.title: Take the Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to deliver a cake to Maellard's birthday party.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: Sandwich of Death
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to find a cure for the Death Sandwich before Benson dies.

added.title: Limousine Lunchtime
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean Maellard's limo before he gets back from vacation.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: Last Meal
added.description: Muscle Man wants to eat his favorite foods before going on a diet.

added.title: Steak Me Amadeus
added.description: Mordecai wants to ask Margaret to be his girlfriend.

added.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
added.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

added.title: Ben 10,000
added.description: Ben gets sucked into the future by a grown up Gwen. His mission is to help the now all powerful and adult Ben 10,000 seemingly defeat the future versions of Dr. Animo and Vilgax. However, the real reason Ben has been brought to the future is to teach his adult self some humility and the fact he's lost touch with Max and has forgotten what's really important, family.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Gone Fishin'
added.description: When their fishing trip in Undertown takes a bizarre twist, Ben, Rook, and Grandpa Max, begin their search for a ship-bottling alien pirate who has captured Magister Patelliday. (Introducing Capt. Cork.)

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: Showdown Part I
added.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Bengeance is Mine
added.description: Vilgax' former lackey Psyphon is elated when his master returns.

added.title: Weapon XI Part 2
added.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

added.title: Vreedlemania
added.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 2
added.description: Ben and Dr. Psychobos become reluctant allies in a parallel-dimension maelstrom.

added.title: Under a Red Sun
added.description: Steppenwolf "boom tubes" Superman to a planet with a red sun in order to make the Man of Steel powerless. Somehow Batman and Big Barda have to locate the planet before Superman is destroyed.

added.title: Los Vegetales
added.description: Gumball y Darwin solo quieren holgazanear todo el día, pero terminan teniendo que salvar al resto de la familia.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Ahora nos estamos separando
added.description: Perla cuenta una historia.

added.title: Cual es tu problema
added.description: Amatista convence a Steven de que se tome un día libre.

added.title: La pregunta
added.description: Steven les muestra a unas gemas citadinas cómo vivían los vaqueros.

added.title: Dama de honor
added.description: Steven tiene una gran sorpresa para las Gemas de Cristal.

added.title: Reunificados
added.description: Steven reúne a todos para un evento especial.

added.title: Piernas del Planeta Madre
added.description: Steven viaja para visitar a su familia.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: Con tantos cambios en su vida, Steven intenta encontrar su lugar en el mundo.

added.title: Juntos Solos
added.description: Steven organiza una fiesta para reunir a su familia.

added.title: Escapismo
added.description: Steven usa sus poderes psíquicos para conseguir ayuda.

added.title: Cambia de Parecer
added.description: Steven se enfrenta al mayor desafío de su vida.

added.title: Unos y Ceros
added.description: Los Titanes construyen un robot con inteligencia artificial para que elabore una pizza que nunca antes fue hecha.

added.title: Dia de los Trabajos
added.description: Robin obliga a los demás Titanes a olvidar sus sueños y a conseguir trabajos normales y aburridos.

added.title: La Maldicion de la Momia
added.description: Los Osos bebé deben devolver una momia a su tumba para no ser víctimas de una maldición eterna.

added.title: El Cumpleanos de Panda
